"use strict";(self.webpackChunkmy_website=self.webpackChunkmy_website||[]).push([[8494],{2813:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"greetings","metadata":{"permalink":"/qs-research/blog/greetings","editUrl":"https://github.com/facebook/docusaurus/tree/main/packages/create-docusaurus/templates/shared/blog/2024-07-11-second-blog/2024-07-11-second-post.md","source":"@site/blog/2024-07-11-second-blog/2024-07-11-second-post.md","title":"Generative AI Newsletter - July 11, 2024","description":"Generative AI Newsletter - July 11, 2024","date":"2024-07-11T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"weekly newsletter","permalink":"/qs-research/blog/tags/Weekly_Newsletter","description":"Tag description"}],"readingTime":3.24,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Oliver Camp","title":"blank","url":"https://github.com/blahdude","image_url":"https://github.com/blahdude.png","imageURL":"https://github.com/blahdude.png"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"greetings","title":"Generative AI Newsletter - July 11, 2024","authors":[{"name":"Oliver Camp","title":"blank","url":"https://github.com/blahdude","image_url":"https://github.com/blahdude.png","imageURL":"https://github.com/blahdude.png"}],"tags":["weekly newsletter"]},"unlisted":false,"nextItem":{"title":"Generative AI Newsletter - July 3, 2024","permalink":"/qs-research/blog/greetings"}},"content":"![Generative AI Newsletter - July 11, 2024](./QS_Email_Header_1_words.png)\\n\\nHello QuinStreet Team,\\n\\nWelcome to this week\'s edition of QuinStreet\u2019s Generative AI Newsletter. I\'m thrilled to share the latest updates and trends that are currently shaping the AI landscape. This week\u2019s newsletter goes over recent AI developments from the past week, including new tools, features, and industry insights.\\n\\nAlso, the QuinStreet Generative AI Database site is currently in beta: [Link](https://blahdude.github.io/qs-research/)\\n\\n**The AI Conference 2024: Shaping the Future of AI**\\n\\n- [***September 10th and 11th in San Francisco, California***](https://aiconference.com/)\\n- Two days with the brightest minds in AI, featuring three tracks and over 60 speakers, where they\'ll explore AI alongside passionate engineers, researchers, and like-minded individuals, fostering connections at the forefront of innovation.\\n\\n**Figma AI**\\n\\n- **Waitlist Opportunity**: Request to join the waitlist for access to Figma\'s UI3 AI capabilities. (Note: I am still on the waitlist and will give a more comprehensive review once I get access, they randomize who gets access)\\n  - To join, click the bottom right \u201c?\u201d icon in your Figma project, then click join waitlist.\\n\\n**Useful GPT\u2019s**\\n\\nComprehensive guide to the best GPTs to use with ChatGPT.\\n- [**Email GPT**](https://chatgpt.com/g/g-SLkL4uUYY-email)\\n  - Assists in creating and revising emails in your desired tone.\\n  - Helps clear your inbox quicker and respond professionally.\\n- [**Canva GPT**](https://chatgpt.com/g/g-alKfVrz9K-canva)\\n  - Solid tool for finding inspiration for presentations, landing pages, and social media posts.\\n- [**Briefly**](https://chat.openai.com/g/g-LNsEQH5rz-briefly)\\n  - Condenses your text, retaining accurate information every time.\\n  - Requires 0 prompt manipulation, just insert your text and it will adjust it.\\n- [**Prompt Perfect**](https://chatgpt.com/g/g-0QDef4GiE-prompt-perfect)\\n  - Interactive guide to creating and improving prompts.\\n  - Type \u201cStart\u201d to view its capabilities.\\n- [**Consensus**](https://chatgpt.com/g/g-bo0FiWLY7-consensus)\\n  - Derive any answer you want from relevant and accurate sources\\n  - Perplexity-like AI-search engine\\n- ***Bonus:***\\n  - [**Tutor Me by Khan Academy**](https://chatgpt.com/g/g-hRCqiqVlM-tutor-me)\\n    - Personalized tutoring in any subject.\\n  - [**Books GPT**](https://chatgpt.com/g/g-z77yDe7Vu-books)\\n    - Easily find books and reading recommendations.\\n\\n**New Tools and Updates:**\\n\\n- [**Claude\'s new artifact**](https://x.com/AnthropicAI/status/1810698780263563325) features offer enhanced capabilities for managing and analyzing digital assets with improved efficiency and precision.\\n- Meta released their new [**Multi-Token Prediction models**](https://huggingface.co/facebook/multi-token-prediction)\\n- [**Moshi**](https://moshi-ai.com/): French AI lab Kyutai released Moshi, an open-source GPT-4 alternative.\\n- Text to 3D: Meta AI introduced [**3D Gen**](https://ai.meta.com/research/publications/meta-3d-gen/), a pipeline for text-to-3D asset generation, useful for product/object placement in ads.\\n- [**RouteLLM**](https://lmsys.org/blog/2024-07-01-routellm/): A new technique that selects models at inference time based on performance.\\n- [**Voice AI**](https://voice.ai/): AI audio startup Voice AI showcased new capabilities.\\n- [**Apple Research**](https://pub.towardsai.net/inside-4m-21-apple-small-model-that-works-across-21-modalities-2416ab96a39e): Investing heavily in small on-device multimodal AIs with the 4M-21 model\\n- [**Latitude**](https://www.latitude.sh/): Deploy AI models on NVIDIA GPUs over the cloud without traditional complexities.\\n\\n**Industry Developments**\\n\\n- [**Breaking OpenAI News**](https://www.ft.com/content/ecfa69df-5d1c-4177-9b14-a3a73072db12): Microsoft and Apple drop OpenAI seats amid antitrust scrutiny\\n- [**Venture Capital Surge**](https://news.crunchbase.com/ai/musk-ai-xai-wayve-coreweave/): AI startups captured over $18 billion in venture funding in Q2 2024, with notable mega-funding rounds for companies like xAI, CoreWeave, and Scale AI.\\n\\n**Global Developments**\\n\\n- [**OpenAI\'s Access Restrictions in China**](https://www.theguardian.com/world/article/2024/jul/09/chinese-developers-openai-blocks-access-in-china-artificial-intelligence): OpenAI notified its Chinese users that access to its tools and services would be blocked starting July 9.\\n- [**Generative AI Adoption**](https://news.crunchbase.com/ai/musk-ai-xai-wayve-coreweave/): A survey revealed China as a global leader in generative AI adoption, with 83% of respondents in China reporting use, compared to 65% in the U.S. and a global average of 54%.\\n\\n**Investment and Startup News**\\n\\n- For AI enthusiasts, here are the latest funding rounds from the past week. Keeping track of these updates is an excellent way to identify the newest and most innovative projects in the AI space.\\n  - [**Magic**](https://www.pymnts.com/artificial-intelligence-2/2024/report-ai-video-startup-runway-looking-to-raise-450-million/): An AI coding startup raising about $200 million at a reported $1.5 billion valuation.\\n  - [**Runway**](https://www.pymnts.com/artificial-intelligence-2/2024/report-ai-video-startup-runway-looking-to-raise-450-million/): AI generative video company looking to raise $450 million.\\n  - [**Robinhood**](https://newsroom.aboutrobinhood.com/robinhood-acquires-pluto-ai-investment-research-platform/): Acquired AI investment research platform Pluto.\\n  - [**BitMagic**](https://venturebeat.com/ai/bitmagic-raises-4m-for-ai-platform-that-generates-3d-games-from-consumer-prompts/): Raised $4 million for its text-to-game platform.\\n  - [**Captions**](https://slator.com/ai-video-startup-captions-valued-at-usd-500m-in-usd-60m-series-c/#:~:text=AI%20video%20editing%20startup%20Captions,also%20pegged%20at%20USD%20500m.): Raised $60 million for their AI-powered video creation and editing platform.\\n\\nStay tuned for more updates and detailed insights into the evolving world of AI.\\n\\nBest regards,\\n\\nOliver Camp"},{"id":"greetings","metadata":{"permalink":"/qs-research/blog/greetings","editUrl":"https://github.com/facebook/docusaurus/tree/main/packages/create-docusaurus/templates/shared/blog/2024-06-03-first-blog/2024-06-03-first-post.md","source":"@site/blog/2024-06-03-first-blog/2024-06-03-first-post.md","title":"Generative AI Newsletter - July 3, 2024","description":"Generative AI Newsletter - July 3, 2024","date":"2024-06-03T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"weekly newsletter","permalink":"/qs-research/blog/tags/Weekly_Newsletter","description":"Tag description"}],"readingTime":4.49,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Oliver Camp","title":"blank","url":"https://github.com/blahdude","image_url":"https://github.com/blahdude.png","imageURL":"https://github.com/blahdude.png"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"greetings","title":"Generative AI Newsletter - July 3, 2024","authors":[{"name":"Oliver Camp","title":"blank","url":"https://github.com/blahdude","image_url":"https://github.com/blahdude.png","imageURL":"https://github.com/blahdude.png"}],"tags":["weekly newsletter"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Generative AI Newsletter - July 11, 2024","permalink":"/qs-research/blog/greetings"}},"content":"![Generative AI Newsletter - July 3, 2024](./QS_Email_Header_1_words.png)\\n\\nHello QuinStreet Team,\\n\\nWelcome to this week\'s edition of QuinStreet\u2019s Generative AI Newsletter. I\u2019m excited to bring you the latest updates and trends shaping the AI landscape. From insightful industry reports to groundbreaking tool releases, here\'s a comprehensive overview of the significant AI developments from the past few weeks.\\n\\nAlso, the QuinStreet Generative AI Database site is currently in beta and should be accurate/up to date sometime next week: https://blahdude.github.io/qs-research/\\n\\n**Figma Config**\\n  - *AI Beta Exploration*: Figma wrapped up its Config conference last week, unveiling various AI tools which they will slowly release to users throughout the year. Users can now explore the Figma AI Beta. [Join the beta](https://www.figma.com/community/file/1375505114072192161)\\n  - *Controversial Feature*: Figma\'s \\"Make Design\\" AI tool faced criticism for producing outputs similar to Apple\u2019s weather app, leading to its removal. [Learn more](https://siliconangle.com/2024/07/02/figma-disables-new-ai-tool-repeatedly-cloned-apples-weather-app/)\\n  - *Model Training*: Figma users have until August 15th to decide on the usage of their designs for AI training. [Learn more](https://siliconangle.com/2024/07/02/figma-disables-new-ai-tool-repeatedly-cloned-apples-weather-app/)\\n\\n**New Tools and Updates**\\n  - *Claude 3.5 Sonnett*: New Anthropic model sets new benchmarks for graduate level reasoning, undergraduate level knowledge, and coding proficiency. [Try it out](https://www.anthropic.com/news/claude-3-5-sonnet)\\n  - *ChatGPT App*: Desktop ChatGPT app now available to all MacOS users! [Find out more](https://openai.com/chatgpt/mac/)\\n  - *Gemini 1.5 Pro*: The waitlist is now open for developers to access the 2M token context. [Learn more](https://developers.googleblog.com/en/new-features-for-the-gemini-api-and-google-ai-studio/)\\n  - *Gemini Chrome Update*: can now run in Chrome locally/offline. [Example](https://x.com/mortenjust/status/1805190952358650251) Opt in here: [Google Form](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfZXeiwj9KO9jMctffHPym88ln12xNWCrVkMY_u06WfSTulQg/viewform)\\n  - *Runway Gen-3 Alpha*: The most powerful text-to-video model yet has been released. [Check it out](https://runwayml.com/blog/introducing-gen-3-alpha/)\\n  - *MISed*: A new tool for conversing with meeting transcripts, eliminating the need to read entire transcripts or recordings. [Discover more](https://research.google/blog/efficient-data-generation-for-source-grounded-information-seeking-dialogs-a-use-case-for-meeting-transcripts/)\\n  - *Stanford Course*: Stanford professor Andrej Karpathy released a massive course to build AI storytellers using LLM. Designed to provide a deep understanding of AI, LLMs, and deep learning. [Find Course Here](https://github.com/karpathy/LLM101n)\\n\\n**Industry Insights**\\n\\n- A recent report featuring insights from over 700 tech leaders has shed light on the current state of AI and its use cases. Here are some key takeaways:\\n  - *Perception of AI*: 50.3% of tech leaders believe AI is overrated.\\n  - *Investment Gaps*: 40.5% of leadership feels they haven\'t invested sufficiently in AI.\\n  - *Daily Use*: On average, 56.4% use AI copilots daily, with this figure rising to 72% in smaller companies.\\n  - *Adoption Rates*: AI adoption varies across roles, with designers at 39%, project managers at 68%, and engineers at 62.5%.\\n  - *Productivity Boost*: 85% of respondents report increased productivity due to AI.\\n  - *ChatGPT Usage*: 76.7% of the leaders use ChatGPT regularly.\\n- For more detailed insights, [read the full report](https://retool.com/blog/reports/state-of-ai-h1-2024?utm_source=alphasignal&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=as_main_ad).\\n\\n**Industry Developments**\\n\\n  - *Apple and AI Deals*: Apple is exploring AI deals beyond OpenAI, including with Meta and Google. [More details](https://aibreakfast.beehiiv.com/p/apple-cutting-deal-google-ai)\\n  - *Leading AI Models*: ChatGPT-4o and Claude 3.5 Sonnett are excelling in image analysis. [Find out more](https://aibreakfast.beehiiv.com/p/apple-cutting-deal-google-ai)\\n  - *AI Safety Benchmarking*: Anthropic introduced a new benchmarking program for LLM safety. [Learn about it](https://www.mindstream.news/p/anthropics-initiative-ai-safety-revealed)\\n  - *AI-Generated Lawsuits*: The rise of AI-generated lawsuits is here. [Read more](https://www.mindstream.news/p/anthropics-initiative-ai-safety-revealed)\\n\\n**Global Developments**\\n\\n  - *China\'s AI Patent Surge*: China has filed six times more generative AI patents than the US, showcasing diverse applications across industries. [Read the report](https://www.wipo.int/pressroom/en/articles/2024/article_0009.html)\\n\\n**New Models and Datasets on Hugging Face**\\n\\n- Hugging Face is an open-source AI model platform that streamlines AI implementation\\n  - *MARS5*: A cutting-edge speech model capable of generating diverse prosody with just 5 seconds of audio and a text snippet. [Explore MARS5](https://huggingface.co/CAMB-AI/MARS5-TTS)\\n    - Use cases include call centers, ads, and voice overs.\\n  - *PersonaHub*: A versatile dataset for training models on synthetic data tailored for various personas. [Learn more](https://huggingface.co/datasets/proj-persona/PersonaHub)\\n    - Use cases include chatbots, content creation, and analytics.\\n\\n**Investment and Startup News**\\n\\n- For AI enthusiasts, here are the latest funding rounds from the past week. Keeping track of these updates is an excellent way to identify the newest and most innovative projects in the AI space.\\n  - **Stability AI** raised a new funding round and appointed Prem Akkaraju as CEO. [Learn More](https://stability.ai/news/stability-ai-secures-significant-new-investment)\\n  - **Orby AI** secured $30 million to develop extensive action models. [Learn More](https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2024/06/27/2905144/0/en/Orby-AI-Raises-30-Million-to-Deliver-the-First-Large-Action-Model-for-AI-Automation-Unlocking-Unrivaled-Enterprise-Efficiencies.html)\\n  - **Day.ai** garnered $4 million from Sequoia for an AI-centric CRM. [Learn More](https://day.ai/sequoia-backs-ai-native-crm)\\n  - **Axelera** raised $68 million for edge AI chip development. [Learn More](https://venturebeat.com/ai/axelera-raises-68m-to-rival-nvidia-with-edge-ai-chips/)\\n  - **Etched** obtained $120 million for transformer-specialized chips. [Learn More](https://www.reuters.com/technology/artificial-intelligence/ai-startup-etched-raises-120-million-develop-specialized-chip-2024-06-25/)\\n  - **Emergence** acquired $97.2 million for its agent platform. [Learn More](https://techcrunch.com/2024/06/24/emergence-thinks-it-can-crack-the-ai-agent-code/?guccounter=1&guce_referrer=aHR0cHM6Ly90aGVzZXF1ZW5jZS5zdWJzdGFjay5jb20v&guce_referrer_sig=AQAAAH7mRHjDoXoIHws5dKi3fkHhX42uL0-TV3nOHjD2afvwIBBr0A7-Mp6gnFBERcybMit1uKM8biTSmyNYQZubMjwGNpdKrbkLQHjgcC76OfzV0kEL8FblRoUBkGnY1XTWtErzLLYgLHASN0UwLL9RJWnCa5UVI8lOsUN42cONHMq3)\\n  - **EvolutionaryScale** secured $142 million for a new AI model in protein discovery. [Learn More](https://www.biopharma-reporter.com/Article/2024/06/27/evolutionaryscale-raises-142m-and-launches-ai-model-for-protein-discovery)\\n  - **Kleiner Perkins** raised $2 billion for startups leveraging generative AI. [Learn More](https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-06-28/kleiner-perkins-pulls-in-more-than-2-billion-for-new-funds?srnd=technology-ai)\\n  - AI e-commerce platform **Daydream** secured $50 million in new funding. [Learn More](https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/daydream-secures-50-million-in-seed-funding-to-launch-new-ai-powered-search-and-discovery-shopping-platform-302177481.html)\\n  - **illumex** raised $13 million for data governance in generative AI. [Learn More](https://illumex.ai/press/illumex-raises-13m-to-enable-trustworthy-governed-enterprise-genai-with-structured-data/)\\n  - **SoftBank** invested in Perplexity at a $3 billion valuation. [Learn More](https://www.reuters.com/technology/artificial-intelligence/softbank-invest-search-startup-perplexity-ai-3-bln-valuation-bloomberg-reports-2024-06-27/)\\n  - **Hebbia** raised $100 million in Series B funding for document search. [Learn More](https://techcrunch.com/2024/06/27/hebbia-raises-nearly-100m-seriesb-for-ai-powered-document-search-led-by-andreessen-horowitz/)\\n  - **Oracle** announced new in-database LLM capabilities. [Learn More](https://www.oracle.com/news/announcement/oracle-announces-in-database-llms-and-automated-in-database-vector-store-with-heatwave-genai-2024-06-26/)\\n  - **SoftBank** partnered with Tempus to invest in healthcare AI. [Learn More](https://group.softbank/en/news/press/20240627)\\n  - **Andrew Ng** is raising $120 million for his next AI fund. [Learn More](https://techcrunch.com/2024/06/27/andrew-ng-plans-to-raise-120m-for-next-ai-fund/)\\n  - **Creatio** raised $200 million for its AI low-code platform. [Learn More](https://www.creatio.com/company/news/creatio-capital-raise-2024)\\n  - **Nubank** acquired AI banking platform Hyperplane. [Learn More](https://international.nubank.com.br/company/nubank-acquires-hyperplane-to-accelerate-ai-first-strategy/)\\n  - **Dappier** raised $2 million for an LLM content marketplace. [Learn More](https://dappier.com/2024/06/26/dappier-funding-ai-data-rights/)\\n  - **Substrate** obtained $8 million for its modular AI platform. [Learn More](https://venturebeat.com/ai/substrate-lands-8m-funding-to-bring-lego-blocks-approach-to-enterprise-ai/)\\n\\nStay tuned for more updates and detailed insights into the evolving world of AI.\\n\\nBest regards,\\n\\nOliver Camp"}]}}')}}]);